t qualify as a structural heading. Now I'm checking whether \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" has a higher raw score to become the best structural heading.\n\nAfter filtering by threshold and deduplication, I need to see what ends up in `selected`. Looking at `allCapsSelected` after threshold and dedup, if both \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" and \"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\" survive, I'm checking whether \"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\" qualifies as a sub-header by looking at what comes after it in the original lines—if the next line starts with a digit, that would indicate it's a sub-header. But I also need to account for \"CHLEBEK\" being all-caps, which complicates whether the sub-header logic applies.\n\nThe dedup rule is the key issue here: when one title is a substring of another, it keeps the shorter one. Since \"CHLEBEK\" is a substring of \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" and is shorter, the dedup logic removes the longer string and keeps just \"CHLEBEK\". This is the bug—\"CHLEBEK\" appears as a standalone line on line 9, so the dedup incorrectly prioritizes it over the more complete title.\n\nNow I'm checking the `firstStructuralHeading` prefix removal logic. I'm testing whether \"CHLEBEK\" is a space-delimited prefix of the structural heading by checking if the full title starts with \"CHLEBEK \" followed by a space. The check confirms this is true, so \"CHLEBEK\" should actually be filtered out by the prefix removal at lines 440-448. But something's preventing that from happening.\n\nThe issue is that the prefix filter only activates when the full structural heading is already in the selected array. If \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" is present in selected at that point, the prefix filter would remove \"CHLEBEK\". However, the dedup algorithm runs after the prefix filter, and since dedup favors shorter titles, it's picking \"CHLEBEK\" over the full title. I need to trace through the exact order of operations: prefix filtering happens first at line 440, then continu