{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WNCzra9YegyxfnAA4RidRZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No diagnostic logs available. Let me write the feedback based on my analysis.\n\nLet me think carefully about both failures:\n\n**Failure 1: CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM → Got: CHLEBEK**\n\nThe document structure:\n- Line 1 (idx 0): \"Lato | Dania główne\"\n- Line 2 (idx 1): \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"\n- Line 3 (idx 2): \"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\"\n- Lines 4-8 (idx 3-7): ingredient lines starting with numbers\n\n\n- Line 9 (idx 8): \"CHLEBEK\" (appears again as a section header)\n- Lines 10-13: more ingredients\n- Line 14: \"świeżo zmielony pieprz\"\n- Lines 15-18: timing information like \"DLA 4 OSÓB\", \"PRZYGOTOWANIE 1 GODZ. 45 MIN\", \"GOTOWANIE 30 MIN\", \"OCZEKIWANIE 1 GODZ. 30 MIN\"\n\nThe issue is that \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" is a 6-word title, but the extraction is stopping at the first word because \"CHLEBEK\" appears again later as a section header, which is confusing the extraction logic. The short all-caps candidates dominate the ranking and push the longer \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" out of the 25-candidate pool entirely. Once it's cut, it never gets embedded in the structural candidates, so `firstStructuralHeading` becomes something else or null, the prefix filter never triggers, and \"CHLEBEK\" alone wins as the top all-caps match instead. Now looking at the second failure case with \"Faszerowana papryka\" where the output was \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\" instead. The issue is that my metadata detection only recognizes English patterns like \"SERVES\" or \"MAKES\", so Polish phrases like \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\" (meaning \"for 3 peppers\") slip through as potential titles. Even though the bilingual detection should filter out \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\", the all-caps bonus still gives \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\" an unfair advantage over the actual title \"Faszerowana papryka\", and my guard checking for a single all-caps selection isn't catching this edge case.\n\nThe root problems are that I'm not detecting Polish-specific metadata patterns, the all-caps bonus is too generous for section headers, the pre-filter's preference for shorter candidates can exclude legitimate multi-word titles, and short all-caps headers are competing too effectively against mixed-case actual recipe names. Now I'm documenting these findings.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":129,"cache_read_input_tokens":53386,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":129},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bb9abb27-5877-4e65-9635-9fb1a076739a","uuid":"29c00478-f875-4289-85c1-259e69a7599c"}
